,Recommended,209230,18816832,"Posted: 1 November, 2015",all,CPA,"Not the best hidden object game out there, but good enough that you'll want to finish it.  It does have a couple interesting tack-ons, such as the Elements, and a couple tough puzzles, particularly towards the end.Art is decent and I didn't find the HO scenes too dark, which can absolutely ruin a HO game.There are only two difficulty levels - Easy and Hard.  Hard is more like Casual in other HO games.  Hints are available, and without penalty, an auto-hint will alert your next move if you take too long in a room, and the map notates rooms that have a current puzzle or object available.As a couple others have stated, the story is rather ludicrous, but worst is the voice acting.  Now, Frogwares, I'm sure you didn't have a large budget for the voice acting, but you could have at least had the actors slow down a little and use the punctuation properly when they were speaking.  It was like they were speed reading the script.Lastly, I was very disappointed with the end.  It just kind of...ended."
